properties.description:
Takura (west of Hervey Bay) – bushfire as at 2pm Sun 3 May 
Queensland Fire and Emergency Services (QFES) crews remain on scene at a bushfire burning between Mungomery Road and Burgowan Road, Takura. This fire is contained and there is no threat to property at this time. This blaze is expected to smoulder for several days and firefighters will continue to monitor the area. Residents in Hervey Bay, Dundowran, Takura, Craignish and Toogoom areas may be affected by smoke. If affected, residents are asked to close windows and doors. Those suffering from a respiratory condition should keep their medications close by. Motorists should drive with caution and to conditions. If residents are concerned their property is under threat they are advised to call Triple Zero (000) immediately.
